      • fromNominalColorTemperature

        public static CIEIlluminantDSpectrum fromNominalColorTemperature(double t)
        Creates a new CIEIlluminantDSpectrum corresponding to the provided nominal color temperature (i.e., the temperature suggested by the name of a standard illuminant. For example: 6500K for D65). This differs slightly from correlated color temperature (see Why 6504K?).
        Parameters:
        t - The correlated color temperature (in Kelvin).
        Returns:
        The CIE Illuminant D spectral power distribution with the specified correlated color temperature.
        See Also:
        Illuminant D65 - Why 6504K?
